HEADWORD: Limy
<hw>Lim"y</hw> <pr>(l⟦imac⟧m"⟦ycr⟧)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[See 4th
<er>Lime</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Smeared with, or consisting of,
lime; viscous.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Limy</xex> snares.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Containing lime; <as>as, a <ex>limy</ex>
soil</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Resembling lime; having the qualities of
lime.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lin</ent>⟦br⟧
